Alexander Bard:

" we find relations relations relations everywhere. Whitehead's relationalism.
But how these relations are perceived and processed and reacted to varies enormously.
So attaching the human "psyche" in any form to everything makes little or no sense. Psyche is not even key to psyche itself.
Better to go deep on relationalism. Which when you consider that everything is in flux has a name.
And its name is dialectics. Therefore pandialecticism as the only pan worthy of the pan.
Matter is no pan, that's for sure. Matter is just actualized physical potentia. Its own emergence vector for sure but no pan."

